This directory contains a snapshot of the currently working version
of the RML system, an executable specification language for using
Natural Semantics in programming language implementations.

Please read the file INSTALL for installation instructions.

Please read the file NEWS for a summary of user-visible changes
made in each intermediate release.

Please read the file PROBLEMS for a list of known bugs in the RML compiler
and its runtime libraries. Please read config/PROBLEMS for a list of
known problems with certain operating systems and C compilers.

The elisp directory contains a simple RML mode for Gnu Emacs.

The examples hierarchy contains some working applications constructed
using RML.

COPYRIGHT contains the RML copyright notice, license and disclaimer.

More information about RML can be found in
http://www.ida.liu.se/~pelab/rml
or by contacting the author.

Author:2002-2008 (versions above rml-2.1.8)
